openafs at stanford information technology services skip to page content service navigation search search this site stanford university information technology services primary links home page stanford university it services service catalog it services all providers status & metrics it services metrics alerts systems monitoring help request status about us contact info organization chart strategic plan jobs user login why login its internal expand menus hide menus expand site navigation hide site navigation openafs at stanford home openafs at stanford overview it services packages openafs client software for both windows xp vista windows 7 and mac os x this software provides an alternative to sftp clients like securefx and fetch for people who frequently access files in afs space the client software is not something that it services develops openafs is an actively developed open source project that produces frequent updates to the client and server software it services evaluates new updates and produces installers to configure the client for use with the stanford afs infrastructure and to provide a simple gui application to allow users to easily mount afs directories if you need to occasionally update a personal or department web page you will likely be better off using webafs the web based interface to afs or an sftp client like securefx for windows and fetch for mac os x available to current faculty staff and students features allows users to directly access and edit files stored in afs as opposed to copying the file to a local drive editing it and then copying it back to the server can be kept updated automatically via stanford desktop tools requirements kerberos for windows or the kerberos configuration utility for macintosh data security restrictions may be used to transmit restricted and confidential data as defined by the stanford university information security office support the openafs clients distributed through this site have been tested by it services and found to generally work on the same systems that are used to test the essential stanford software ess applications however users have traditionally encountered more issues with this software than with the ess offerings where possible it services will report problems that are found to the openafs developers in order to help improve future versions of the clients for assistance please submit a helpsu request rates free of charge getting started to obtain the openafs client software and learn more about os specific issues please see the following pages openafs for windows openafs for mac os x last modified fri 18 nov 2011 at 15 35 pages about this service overview openafs 1.5 for windows using stanford openafs for windows openafs 1.6 for macintosh using stanford openafs for macintosh find answers submit a helpsu request stanford answers related pages kerberos for windows kerberos configuration utiility for macintosh afs at stanford footer links stanford university helpsu user login stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
